Chile to Submit Bill to Change Consumer Credit Rate Ceiling

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-08-31T19:59:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/chile-to-submit-bill-to-change-consumer-credit-rate-ceiling.html
Chile’s government will submit a
bill to Congress next week to modify the maximum rate that can
be charged on consumer loans, the  Finance Ministry  said in an e-
mailed statement today.  Chile’s government has not yet decided on a new ceiling for
consumer credit rates, which currently exceeds 50 percent, the
statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Faries at 
 wfaries@bloomberg.net . 